definition.value: A galloyl-beta-D-glucose compound having five galloyl groups in the 1-, 2-, 3-, 4- and 6-positions.
Adenine substituted with a methyl group at position N-1.

A member of the class of coumarins that is 2H-chromen-2-one substituted by a [(1R,2R,3S,5S)-2-(2-carboxyethyl)-2,5-dimethyl-3-(2-methylprop-1-en-1-yl)cyclopentyl]methoxy group at position 7. It is isolated from the roots of Ferula sinaica.
Any polysaccharide containing a substantial proportion of aminomonosaccharide residues.
An indoleacetaldehyde that is acetaldehyde in which one of the methyl hydrogens are replaced by a indol-3-yl group. It is an intermediate metabolite in the metabolism of tryptophan.
